All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Forwarder
    The forwarder represents an abstraction for all outgoing network connections from the message bus.
    MessageBus
    MessageBus is the interface with which the application interacts with the messaging framework.
    MessageBusController
    The MessageBusController class represents the controlling class of the messaging framework.
    MessageBusControllerTest  
    MessageBusFactory
    Factory used for configuring and creating a messaging bus.
    MessageBusFactoryTest  
    MessageConverter
    The MessageConverter class is a pure utility class used for dealing with Json and conversion between Json and java objects.
    MessageConverterTest  
    MessageDeliverer
    A thread delivering message objects to the application in a synchronous way.
    MessageDelivery<MessageType>
    A class holding relevant data for the delivery of a message to the application.
    MessageHandler<MessageType>
    The MessageListener interface is provided by the messaging framework and has to be implemented by the application in order for the messaging framework to be useful.
    MessageIdStorage
    A class keeping track of received messages.
    MessageIdStorageTest  
    MessagePackage
    The MessagePackage class is used to wrap any java object inside a normed package and provide meta data for the propagation between peers.
    Receiver
    The Receiver class is an abstraction for a server socket.
    Sender
    The Sender class is an abstraction for a client Socket.
    SubscriptionService
    A class keeping track of subscribed message types.
    TestMessage
